      • getOutputRecord

        OutputRecord getOutputRecord(InputRecord input)
        Creates an OutputRecord object designed for this link.

        The typical use of this method is to perform read-modify-write operations with a given InputRecord object. The created OutputRecord allows for users to update the interested columns of input record, and write it to this output link.

        Parameters:
        input - A InputRecord. If null the function returns null.
        Returns:
        A new OutputRecord object, or null if this method is invoked for reject output link.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if input is null.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if called at design time.
        See Also:
        writeRecord(OutputRecord record)

      • getRejectRecord

        Returns:

      • writeRecord

        void writeRecord(OutputRecord record)
        Writes a record to this output stream link.
        Parameters:
        record - An OutputRecord to be sent through the link. If null the function returns immediately.
        Throws:
        ClassCastException - if unmatched type of object is included in a given record.
        IllegalStateException - if the processor has not been initialized.
        IllegalArgumentException - if record is null, or record was not created for this link.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if called at design time.
        See Also:
        getOutputRecord(), getOutputRecord(InputRecord input)

      • writeWaveMarker

        void writeWaveMarker()
        Writes a wave marker to this output stream link or reject link. If user's Processor code calls this method without setting Capabilities.setIsWaveGenerator(boolean) = true, the warning messages will be logged on Director. Writing wave marker is supported by Parallel canvas only. In case of server canvas, this call will be ignored.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the processor has not been initialized.
        UnsupportedOperationException - if called at design time.
        See Also:
        Capabilities.setIsWaveGenerator(boolean)

        Returns:
        true if Runtime Column Propagation is enabled on this link. Otherwise, false.
